    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Roofing nails having a plain shank and a lead cap or washer, used for attaching corrugated or other metal roofing. The advantage of using lead washers is that they make a tight joint and prevent leaking and rusting at the nail hole; given that the lead washer is soft, it conforms to the curve and irregular surface of the metal.</Note_Text>
